ABU DHABI, United Arab Emirates, July 18, 2022/APO Group/ --
                                                        
                            The UAE strongly condemned the terrorist attack that targeted a hotel in the city of Jowhar in southern Somalia, which resulted in deaths and injuries, including government officials, and extensive damage to nearby buildings and shops. 
                                The Ministry expressed its sincere condolences and sympathy to the government and people of the Federal Republic of Somalia
                            



The Ministry of Foreign Affairs and International Cooperation (MoFAIC) affirmed that the UAE expresses its strong condemnation of these criminal acts, and its permanent rejection of all forms of violence and terrorism aimed at destabilizing security and stability in contravention of human values and principles. 

The Ministry expressed its sincere condolences and sympathy to the government and people of the Federal Republic of Somalia and to the families of the victims of this heinous crime, as well as its wishes for a speedy recovery for the injured.